    body: "Synderesis (sometimes spelled synteresis) is the habitual knowledge of the first principles of practical reason — above all, 'Good is to be done and pursued, and evil is to be avoided' (St. Thomas Aquinas, ST I-II, q.94, a.2). It is not a virtue acquired through practice but an innate disposition of the intellect, present in every human being by nature. Synderesis cannot err in its general principles, though the application of those principles to particular situations (the work of conscience) can be mistaken. It is the foundation upon which the natural law is built and the ground of all moral reasoning. Synderesis is what makes moral discourse possible between persons of different cultures and religions, because it is a universal endowment of human nature.",
